    description:
      "The Vuntut Gwitchin First Nation, a self-governing Indigenous community in Old Crow, Yukon, has a provision in its constitution requiring that all members of its governance council reside on the settlement land in Old Crow. Angela Dickson, a Vuntut Gwitchin citizen living in Whitehorse, is nominated for council but is disqualified under the residency requirement. She challenges the provision, arguing it violates her s.15 equality rights based on analogous ground of residency (or 'Aboriginality-residence'). The First Nation argues that the residency requirement is essential to self-governance and that s.25 shields their governance decisions from Charter challenge. Analyze the tension between individual Charter rights and collective Indigenous rights.",
    weekReference: "Winter Week 12",
